[ edit ] List of Presidents of Venezuela

The first numbering column reflects the number of the presidency. Since its creation as a republic in 1812, Venezuela has had a total to date of 74 presidencies: a single person serving a single term beginning with Crist bal Mendoza . The second column reflects uninterrupted time in office served by a single person. For example, Juan Cris stomo Falc n served two consecutive terms and is counted in the first column as both 24th presidency and 25th presidency, but this is counted in the second column as the 20th presidential office. The third column lists the actual numbering of distinct individual presidents. Many of the men listed below became President on a provisional basis as they waited for the arrival of the elected or regular president, such as commonly occurs in the aftermath of a civil war , rebellion , or coup d' tat . As a consequence, other Venezuelan presidential rosters may not choose to include the terms below, citing the extreme brevity of certain terms, unusual circumstances that may have surrounded a president's ascendancy into office, and other factors. The colors shaded about each president indicate the political party affiliation of each President ( see key, below ).

Owing to the profound turmoil of the South American Wars of Independence and the period of Gran Colombia over what is now Venezuela, this page has gaps between 1814 and 1819. The Congress of Angostura appointed Sim n Bolivar "Jefe Supremo de la Rep blica de Venezuela" (Supreme Commander of the Republic of Venezuela) from 1819 until 1830. The list below includes interim 'caretaker' as well as regular serving presidents, and democratically-installed presidents as well as those installed by other means (e.g.; Marcos P rez Jim nez ).
